Kenya Breweries Limited, through its iconic whisky brand, Johnnie Walker, on Tuesday unveiled 20 teams that will compete to win an all-expenses paid Formula 1 Championship trip. The function, which happened at K1 Klub House in Nairobi, was attended by Formula 1 fans. It was presided over by KBL head of premium spirit Grace Nshemeire-Gwaku and EABL national advocacy manager Douglas Duncanson. The 20 teams will be subjected to a month-long competition called 'Kenya Racing Festival'. The festival is a competition that combines both Go-Kart racing and F1 Virtual Reality Simulation.